The paper deals with secure coded computing, which involves information theory and cryptography, making cs.IT the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of secret sharing schemes, which falls under the purview of cs.CR (cryptography and security). The paper also deals with distributed computing, which could fall under cs.DC (distributed, parallel, and cluster computing) and cs.DS (data structures and algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses machine learning algorithms, which could fall under cs.LG (machine learning).
